%I A396874 #7 Jun 13 2026 22:26:15
%S A396874 0,0,0,0,3822,9722905,7491396000
%N A396874 Number of relations on an n-set whose minimum-deletion-to-transitivity equals four.
%C A396874 a(n) counts binary relations R on {1,...,n} such that the minimum number of single-pair deletions required to make R transitive equals 4. Equivalently, R is not transitive, no deletion of one, two, or three ordered pairs from R yields a transitive relation, but there exist four pairs p,q,r,s in R with R \ {p,q,r,s} transitive.
%e A396874 For n=4, the count a(4)=3822 was obtained by exhaustive enumeration over all 2^16 = 65536 binary relations on {1,2,3,4}; for n=5, a(5)=9722905 over all 2^25 = 33554432 relations on {1,2,3,4,5}.
%Y A396874 Cf. A006905, A396664, A396669.
%K A396874 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A396874 0,5
